CONFIDENTIALITY POLICY FOR FLYING CAT

We at ATOD DEVELOPERS value your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal information.
This confidentiality policy explains how we collect, use, and disclose your personal information in connection with your use of Flying Cat (the "Game").

Information We Collect
We collect non-personal information, such as information about your gameplay, including high scores.

How We Use Your Information
We may use the personal information we collect from you to:

Personalize your experience with the Game
Improve the Game and our services
We may use non-personal information for research and analytics purposes to improve the Game and our services.

Security
We take reasonable measures to protect your personal information from loss, theft, misuse, and unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, and destruction.
We use industry-standard security measures to protect your personal information.

Data Consent Policy
Our app is safe for use by both Kids and Parents

Children's Privacy
The Game is intended for everyone, but we do not knowingly collect personal information from children under the age of 13.
If we learn that we have collected personal information from a child under the age of 13, we will promptly take steps to delete that information.

Changes to Our Confidentiality Policy
We may update this confidentiality policy from time to time. 
It is your responsability to review this Policy from time to time to ensure that you continue to agree with all of its terms.

Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about our confidentiality policy, please contact us at atoddvlopers@gmail.com

By using the Game, you agree to the terms of this confidentiality policy.
If you do not agree with the terms of this confidentiality policy, please do not use the Game.
